FspR7APSCommand.name: FspR7APSCommand
FspR7APSCommand.description: Protection Switch commands: Manual or Release. The 'Manual Switch' switches manually from addressed facility to the partner but does not force the traffic onto a broken fiber and it does not block the subsequent automatic functioning of the switch. The 'Release Switch' releases the current switch command. For 'Manual Switch' relevant only if revertivity is supported.

FspR7APSCommandCaps.name: FspR7APSCommandCaps
FspR7APSCommandCaps.description: Protection Switch commands: Manual or Release. The 'Manual Switch' switches manually from addressed facility to the partner but does not force the traffic onto a broken fiber and it does not block the subsequent automatic functioning of the switch. The 'Release Switch' releases the current switch command. For 'Manual Switch' relevant only if revertivity is supported.

FspR7LagFendState.name: FspR7LagFendState
FspR7LagFendState.description: The Partner's state variables for the port, encoded as individual bits, as follows: Bits ordering: - LACP_Activity(0), - LACP_Timeout(1), - Aggregation(2), - Synchronization(3), - Collecting(4), - Distributing(5), - Defaulted(6), - Expired(7)

FspR7LagIdFend.name: FspR7LagIdFend
FspR7LagIdFend.description: LAG ID of the Partner LAG PORT parameters. Concatination of Operational Key, Priority and port number. Uses 4+2+4 bytes. Each byte is represented with 2 octets string. Port LAG ID Parameters field octets contents ----- ------ -------- 1_______1-4_____Key___________(ASCII e.g. '0x00AA') 2_______5-6_____Port Priority_(ASCII e.g. '0x80') 3_______7-10____Port Number___(ASCII e.g. '0x0002') Parameters of the LAG ID are separated by commas, e.g. '00AA,80,0002'

FspR7NCTRouteType.name: FspR7NCTRouteType
FspR7NCTRouteType.description: ROUTE-TYPE = NONE | FIBER | CABLE | BKPLANE | EQPT | PROVND. ROUTE-TYPE parameter indicates the connection type between two ports. If a connection between the two ports is within a module (i.e. Client to Network port), the Route-Type is either provisioned (PROVND) of fixed (EQPT). If the connection is between two ports, then the Route-Type is FIBER, or CABLE, or BKPLANE.

neAINSProvEnabled.name: neAINSProvEnabled
neAINSProvEnabled.description: Global system variable. Automatic IN-Service Provisioning ENAbled flag. This value is controlled by settings in the system configuration file. If Y, entities which are autoprovisioned will be created with an initial state of OOS-AU,AINS. If N, autoprovisioned entities will be created in an ISNR state. Entities in an OOS-AU,AINS state will automatically transition to an in-service state after a continuous interval without any active service affecting conditions. The duration of this interval is equal to that given by the AISPDEFTM attribute at the start of the continuous interval.

neAINSDefaultTimer.name: neAINSDefaultTimer
neAINSDefaultTimer.description: AINS Default Signal Timer. The length of time in minutes for which an entity must be free of service affecting conditions in order to automatically transition from an OOS-AU,AINS state to an inservice state. The value is set via the system configuration file. If the value is set to 0, an entity in the OOS-AU, AINS state will immediately transition to an in-service state.

neSecurityMode.name: neSecurityMode
neSecurityMode.description: The switch for handling Security Mode of a Network Element. It supports basic(1) and enhanced(2) security mode. After switch is performed, a user is forced to change the password using fspUserManagementAuthPrivKey and fspUserManagementAuthPrivKeyOld objects in single set-request, otherwise SNMPv3 access to any MIB object will be denied due to authorization error. Switch from basic(1) to enhanced(2) security mode is allowed always. Switch in opposite direction is allowed only after manual user account removal - only one user account with admin(1) privilege level defined by FspR7SnmpPrivLevel TEXTUAL-CONVENTION must remain. In the basic(1) mode: * minimum password length is 8 characters, * maximum password length is 31 characters, * password cannot contain user name, * user name and password upper-case only, * password contains at least - one alphabetic character (a..z; A..Z); - one numeric character (0..9); - one special character ( ! , @ , # , $ , % , ^ , ( , ) , _ , + , | , ~ , { , } , [ , ] , - , . ) In the enhanced(2) mode: * minimum password lenght is 15 characters, * maximum password lenght is 31 characters, * password cannot contain user name, * user name and password mixed-case supported, * password contains at least - two lowercase alphabetic character (a..z); - two uppercase alphabetic character(A..Z); - two numeric character (0..9); - two special character ( ! , @ , # , $ , % , ^ , ( , ) , _ , + , | , ~ , { , } , [ , ] , - , . )

apsConfigTable.name: apsConfigTable
apsConfigTable.description: This table contains attributes related to the automatic protection switching (APS) functionality.

apsConfigEntry.name: apsConfigEntry
apsConfigEntry.description: An entry in the APS configuration table. There is one entry in this table for each protection group.

apsConfigSDswitching.name: apsConfigSDswitching
apsConfigSDswitching.description: This state controls whether the switch criteria for the APS group will include the SignalDegrade alarm.

apsConfigHoldOffTime.name: apsConfigHoldOffTime
apsConfigHoldOffTime.description: This value controls the switch delay (0 to 90 seconds in 100ms steps) for the protection group. Changing the hold-off time when the timer is active will not affect the active timer. The change will take effect the next time the timer is active.

apsProtGroupStatusTable.name: apsProtGroupStatusTable
apsProtGroupStatusTable.description: This table contains status information related to the automatic protection switching (APS) functionality.

apsProtGroupStatusEntry.name: apsProtGroupStatusEntry
apsProtGroupStatusEntry.description: An entry in the APS status table. There is one entry in this table for each protection group.

apsProtGroupStatusApsType.name: apsProtGroupStatusApsType
apsProtGroupStatusApsType.description: The type of APS implemented in this protection group.

apsProtGroupStatusDirection.name: apsProtGroupStatusDirection
apsProtGroupStatusDirection.description: Indicates whether the APS function is 'unidirectional' (single-ended) or 'bidirectional' (dual-ended).

apsProtGroupStatusRevertiveMode.name: apsProtGroupStatusRevertiveMode
apsProtGroupStatusRevertiveMode.description: Indicates if revertive switching is enable dor disabled.

apsProtGroupStatusProtectionMech.name: apsProtGroupStatusProtectionMech
apsProtGroupStatusProtectionMech.description: The protection type of this protection group.

apsProtGroupStatusWorkingIndex.name: apsProtGroupStatusWorkingIndex
apsProtGroupStatusWorkingIndex.description: The entityIndex of the working section in the APS group.

apsProtGroupStatusProtectionIndex.name: apsProtGroupStatusProtectionIndex
apsProtGroupStatusProtectionIndex.description: The entityIndex of the protection section. The protection section will become the active section when an APS switch occurs (ie, as a result of a failure on the working section).

apsProtGroupStatusProtectionType.name: apsProtGroupStatusProtectionType
apsProtGroupStatusProtectionType.description: This describes the topology and level of the protection (OCH or OM -Level on a ring; Line in PT-PT and Line or Dualhomed on a Feeder).

apsProtFacilityConfigTable.name: apsProtFacilityConfigTable
apsProtFacilityConfigTable.description: This table contains attributes related to the automatic protection switching (APS) functionality on a facility involved in a protection group.

apsProtFacilityConfigEntry.name: apsProtFacilityConfigEntry
apsProtFacilityConfigEntry.description: An entry in the APS configuration table. There is one entry in this table for each facility involved in a protection group

apsProtFacilityConfigSwitchCommand.name: apsProtFacilityConfigSwitchCommand
apsProtFacilityConfigSwitchCommand.description: The switch command action for this facility. A command resulting in a switch event will also cause a change of the facility secondary state and a corresponding condition. Addressed by this command is the active port, the port to switch away from. Since this is a manual switch command, it will not switch if other port suffers from a signalfailure or a signal degrade.

apsProtFacilityConfigInhibitSwitchToProt.name: apsProtFacilityConfigInhibitSwitchToProt
apsProtFacilityConfigInhibitSwitchToProt.description: Inhibit Switch to protection facility. Inhibition blocks an automatic switch to the protection facility. Valid only for the working facility.

apsProtFacilityConfigInhibitSwitchToWork.name: apsProtFacilityConfigInhibitSwitchToWork
apsProtFacilityConfigInhibitSwitchToWork.description: Inhibit Switch to working facility. Inhibition blocks an automatic switch to the working facility. Valid only for the protection facility.

deployProvShelfTable.description: Contains entries for provisioning of shelfs.

deployProvShelfEntry.name: deployProvShelfEntry
deployProvShelfEntry.description: All shelves which are provisioned(or during deployProv) will have an entry in this table.

deployProvShelfRowStatus.name: deployProvShelfRowStatus
deployProvShelfRowStatus.description: This object is used to create, or delete a row in this table. To start process of creating a new shelf, this object is initially set to 'createAndWait'. After this action the state of this object becomes 'notReady'. This object stays in this state until all required objects are not set. Objects which must be set are indicated by special objects with capabilities(provisioningShelfTypeCap -> provisioningShelfType, provisioningShelfAdminCap -> provisioningShelfAdmin). If specjal object exist, the indicated object have to be set by one of values specified in special object. If all required objects are set, state of this object becomes 'notInService'. To create a new shelf, this object have to be set to 'active'.

deployProvShelfType.description: The type of Shelf determines uniquely the number and allowed types of the provisionable dependent entities (modules).

deployProvIfType.description: The TYPE defines the transport service type as wrapper with wrapper layer termination OR else as payload

deployProvIfPayload.name: deployProvIfPayload
deployProvIfPayload.description: The payload of the interface (inside a transport overhead). Relevant e. g. for OTN cards which wrap a payload into an OTU1/2 wrapper.

deployProvIfBehaviour.name: deployProvIfBehaviour
deployProvIfBehaviour.description: The configured behaviour of the interface. If configured as a network interface, the interface will use a WDM laser.

deployProvIfTerminationLevel.name: deployProvIfTerminationLevel
deployProvIfTerminationLevel.description: Signal Tremination Level of Intrusive Access to Header Information. Not used in 7.0, monitoring is one layer higher than TERM level, if applicable. All conditions detected on monitoring layer will not be reported (severity degradated to NR).

deployProvIfAlsMode.name: deployProvIfAlsMode
deployProvIfAlsMode.description: A configuration request for the Automatic Laser Shutdown (ALS) function. Refer to FspR7AlsMode Textual Convention for details.

deployProvIfErrorForwarding.name: deployProvIfErrorForwarding
deployProvIfErrorForwarding.description: A configuration request for the error forwarding function. Refer to FspR7ErrorFwdMode Textual Convention for details.

deployProvIfLaserOffDelayFunction.name: deployProvIfLaserOffDelayFunction
deployProvIfLaserOffDelayFunction.description: A configuration request for the Laser Off Delay function. This function delays turning off the laser as a consequent action to a defect.

deployProvIfTimingSource.name: deployProvIfTimingSource
deployProvIfTimingSource.description: The timing source for this interface. - internal: used in stand-alone, point-to-point topologies stand-alone (dedicated fiber operation). - loopTiming: e.g. used in point-to-point via SONET network and feeder topologies. The default is internal(1).

deployProvIfSigDegThresSonetLine.name: deployProvIfSigDegThresSonetLine

deployProvIfSigDegThresSdhMs.name: deployProvIfSigDegThresSdhMs
deployProvIfSigDegThresSdhMs.description: Block-Error-Based Degradation Definition for SDH (standard integration period). Defined as percentage Background Block Errors (30% default) evaluated over a defined period (SDPER-RS).

deployProvIfSignalDegradePeriod.name: deployProvIfSignalDegradePeriod
deployProvIfSignalDegradePeriod.description: The measurement period in seconds used together with the deployProvIfSigDegThresSdhRegSect based on the block error counting method. The valid range is 2..10, The default being 7.

deployProvIfOtnStuffing.name: deployProvIfOtnStuffing
deployProvIfOtnStuffing.description: Indicates if bit/byte stuffing is used in the transport signal.

deployProvIfSigDegThresOtu.name: deployProvIfSigDegThresOtu

deployProvIfTilt.name: deployProvIfTilt
deployProvIfTilt.description: Change of optical channel power in dB over the complete transmission band

areaIdCapTable.name: areaIdCapTable
areaIdCapTable.description: This table is used to get capabilities for AREAID parameter. Regular cap tables including AREAID show the length of output string. Enumerator YES/NO in regular cap tables shows if there are capabilities or value 0 which means 'no capabilities'. The second index (n) is used to devide the output string to n string blocks. Each block has a maximum of 512 bytes. n = output string / 512.

areaIdCapIndexCap.name: areaIdCapIndexCap
areaIdCapIndexCap.description: Used to display capability value per index. The number of capabilities determines the number of indexes.

nendIpCapTable.name: nendIpCapTable
nendIpCapTable.description: This table is used to get capabilities for NENDIP parameter. Enumerator YES/NO in regular cap tables shows if there are capabilities or no. No values for specific entity means 'no capabilities'. The second index (n) is used to devide the output string to n string blocks. Each block has a maximum of 255 bytes. n = output string / 255.

nendIpCapIndexCap.name: nendIpCapIndexCap
nendIpCapIndexCap.description: Used to display capability value per index. The number of capabilities determines the number of indexes.

areaAidCapTable.name: areaAidCapTable
areaAidCapTable.description: This table is used to get capabilities for AREAAID parameter. Regular cap tables including AREAAID show the length of output string. Enumerator YES/NO in regular cap tables shows if there are capabilities or value 0 which means 'no capabilities'. The second index (n) is used to devide the output string to n string blocks. Each block has a maximum of 255 bytes. n = output string / 255.

areaAidCapIndexCap.name: areaAidCapIndexCap
areaAidCapIndexCap.description: Used to display capability value per index. The number of capabilities determines the number of indexes.
